huffmanEncodingScheme

Class tree

  • java.lang.Object
    • huffmanEncodingScheme.tree

  • public class tree
extends java.lang.Object
    Class defines the single node of Huffman binary tree. Includes the type of node (NODE or LEAF), binary code of node, connections with two children and value of frequency.
    Author:
    Konrad

      • tree

        public tree(tree child_L,
            tree child_R)
        Creates the object of tree class and connects it to two children. This if constructor used to construct the Huffman binary tree. It attributes the NODE type because a node includes the children.
        Parameters:
        child_L - left child of node
        child_R - right child of node
